&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role’s mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a VP of Engineering to lead a world-class organization that makes Guidewheel the default intelligence layer for manufacturing. This role requires a leader who is a true &lt;strong&gt;talent magnet&lt;/strong&gt;—someone whose reputation attracts exceptional engineers and whose leadership keeps them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a &lt;strong&gt;builder who develops builders&lt;/strong&gt;. You balance systems-level judgment with the ability to make fast, high-quality decisions. You don’t just manage; you coach your team to operate independently, creating an environment where the best engineers do the best work of their careers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The outcomes you’ll drive&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build an Engine of Speed: &lt;/strong&gt;Build a culture where technical understanding supports fast, high-judgment decision-making. You ensure the team can debate easily, move fast, and you serve as an admired mentor who keeps a high bar for talent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deliver Elite Velocity:&lt;/strong&gt; Baseline and then drive the team toward elite performance levels (frequent deploys, short lead times, low change-failure rates). Publish a visible velocity dashboard and improve metrics consistently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Net Revenue Retention (NRR):&lt;/strong&gt; Make Engineering a core driver of retention. Ensure velocity and quality directly contribute to customer value, delivering features with a high-quality, customer-obsessed mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World-Class Leadership &amp;amp; Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide the &quot;pastoral care,&quot; coaching, and direction needed for the team to thrive. Ensure engineers have protected focus time, clear direction, and that you earn strong cross-functional respect from Product and Operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
